{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17503398","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17503398"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:00:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:00:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2026"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583117","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583117"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:08:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:08:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2026"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2026","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2026"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.78,0.15,0.01,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2026"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108811"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2026","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2026"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2026"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91174"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"1151"},{"type":"tags","id":"3376"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"31559"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31560"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108811","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108811"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 56-year-old man presents to the outpatient gastroenterology clinic with what he describes as a \u201cvolcanic-like\u201d burning sensation in the lower chest after eating, worsening over the last several years. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination his pulse is 80/min, blood pressure 130/75 mmHg and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. His BMI is 29. The rest of the examination is unremarkable. An oesophago-gastroscopy is performed and a view of the lower oesophagus shown (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Oesophageal squamous cell cancer","Barrett\u2019s oesophagus","Ulcerative oesophagitis","Hiatus hernia","Eosinophilic oesophagitis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis man\u0027s symptoms of retrosternal burning after eating indicate likely gastro-oesophageal reflux disease (GORD). Chronic GORD is one of the key risk factors for development of \u003Cstrong\u003EBarrett\u2019s oesophagus\u003C/strong\u003E, which is characterised by metaplastic change just proximal to the gastro-oesophageal junction (GOJ) where the normal squamous epithelium is replaced by intestinal columnar epithelium. In this case the areas of salmon-pink columnar epithelium can be seen extending some 3 - 4 cms above the cardia with tongues going up into the squamous epithelium. Barrett\u2019s oesophagus can become dysplastic and progress to adenocarcinoma if left untreated. Biopsy results are necessary to confirm this diagnosis or indicate if it has become cancerous.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESquamous cell carcinoma of the oesophagus\u003C/strong\u003E tends to occur in the upper and middle portions of the oesophagus (image 1). These patients more typically present with dysphagia and often have a history of smoking and/or alcohol intake. These tumours can be difficult to identify on endoscopy during the early stages and may require staining with Lugol\u2019s iodine to be visualised.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst this man\u0027s symptoms are consistent with gastro-oesophageal reflux, there is no evidence of inflammatory change. \u003Cstrong\u003EEosinophilic oesophagitis\u003C/strong\u003E tends to occur in younger patients and is associated with dysphagia (Image 2).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough a \u003Cstrong\u003Ehiatal hernia\u003C/strong\u003E may cause similar symptoms, it is diagnosed when there is \u0026gt;2cm proximal dislocation of the GOJ, i.e. the upper margin of the stomach folds can be seen above the diaphragmatic indentation (Image 3).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is no evidence of inflammation or ulceration in the photograph, thus making\u003Cstrong\u003E ulcerative oesophagitis\u003C/strong\u003E an unlikely diagnosis (Image 4).\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Chronic GORD is one of the key risk factors for development of Barrett\u2019s oesophagus, which is characterised by metaplastic change just proximal to the gastro-oesophageal junction (GOJ)."],"references":["Whiteman DC, Kendall BJ. Barrett\u0027s oesophagus: epidemiology, diagnosis and clinical management. Med J Aust. 2016;205(7):317-24. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27681974/","Garud SS, Keilin S, Cai Q, Willingham FF. Diagnosis and management of Barrett\u0027s esophagus for the endoscopist.\u00a0Therap Adv Gastroenterol. 2010;3(4):227-238.\u00a0Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3002583/","Pennathur A, Gibson MK, Jobe BA, Luketich JD. Oesophageal carcinoma. Lancet. 2013;381(9864):400-12. Available at: https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(12)60643-6/fulltext","Shimamura Y, Ikeya T, Marcon N, Mosko JD. Endoscopic diagnosis and treatment of early esophageal squamous neoplasia.\u00a0World J Gastrointest Endosc. 2017;9(9):438-447.\u00a0Available at: https://doi.org/10.4253/wjge.v9.i9.438","Hyun JJ, Bak YT. Clinical significance of hiatal hernia.\u00a0Gut Liver. 2011;5(3):267-277. Available at:\u00a0https://doi.org/10.5009/gnl.2011.5.3.267"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91174"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2026"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"10428"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21948"},{"type":"media","id":"21949"},{"type":"media","id":"21950"},{"type":"media","id":"21951"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"10428","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/10428"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5e855115-50df-4eaf-9796-1a37807cb341.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5e855115-50df-4eaf-9796-1a37807cb341.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":514,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"21948","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21948"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/QGRad0jC5y3GGBZ36Q1fTNJzuHbMtX.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/QGRad0jC5y3GGBZ36Q1fTNJzuHbMtX.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1280,"height":1008}},{"type":"media","id":"21949","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21949"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/HJKMPJH093w6GK7AcwCJ7q4vsm7Qgj.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/HJKMPJH093w6GK7AcwCJ7q4vsm7Qgj.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":586,"height":502}},{"type":"media","id":"21950","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21950"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/65G9kh3k4CYebx5oA7W2oLVWXtKXhU.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/65G9kh3k4CYebx5oA7W2oLVWXtKXhU.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":502,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"21951","links":{"self":